f:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","PENDLE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PENDLE's focus on yield tokenization makes it susceptible to funding rate volatility during DeFi yield farming cycles. The token's correlation with broader DeFi trends creates predictable funding patterns that experienced arbitrageurs can exploit. Aevo's smaller liquidity pool compared to major CEXes often leads to funding rate premiums during PENDLE price movements."}]]}]
10:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PENDLE funding rates on Aevo typically trade at a premium to Binance and OKX during DeFi yield spikes, often reaching +0.1% to +0.3% hourly. The token shows strong correlation with TVL growth in yield farming protocols, creating predictable funding cycles. During periods of high options activity on Aevo, PENDLE perpetual funding can become more volatile due to cross-product hedging flows. Monthly analysis shows funding rates spike most frequently during protocol governance events and yield token launches."}]]}]
11:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The most profitable PENDLE funding arbitrage occurs between Aevo and Binance, with average spreads of 15-25 basis points during normal conditions. Aevo's 1-hour funding frequency allows for more granular position management compared to 8-hour cycles on traditional exchanges. Cross-rollup arbitrage becomes particularly lucrative during Ethereum network congestion when Aevo's dedicated infrastructure maintains lower latency. Traders can also exploit the correlation between PENDLE spot yields and perpetual funding to predict rate direction changes."}]]}]
12:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo's rollup architecture introduces smart contract risks not present on centralized exchanges, requiring careful evaluation of bridge security and validator sets. The platform's smaller liquidity pool means large arbitrage positions can impact funding calculations more significantly than on major CEXes. PENDLE's volatility during yield farming events can lead to rapid funding rate reversals, making position sizing critical. Cross-chain arbitrage requires maintaining USDT balances on multiple networks, increasing capital efficiency requirements and bridge exposure risks."}]]}]
13:["$","$L15",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are PENDLE funding rates calculated on Aevo?","answer":"Aevo calculates and settles PENDLE/USDT funding rates every hour, providing more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour cycles. This allows traders to capture shorter-term rate discrepancies and adjust positions more dynamically during volatile periods."},{"question":"What makes PENDLE funding rates unique on a DeFi-focused platform like Aevo?","answer":"PENDLE's yield tokenization focus creates natural demand during DeFi yield spikes, often leading to persistent funding premiums on Aevo. The platform's combined options and perpetuals ecosystem can amplify funding volatility when traders hedge complex yield strategies across both product types."},{"question":"How does Aevo's rollup architecture affect PENDLE funding rate arbitrage?","answer":"The rollup provides faster settlement and lower fees compared to Ethereum mainnet, enabling profitable arbitrage of smaller funding rate differences. However, it introduces cross-chain risks when arbitraging against CEXes, and the smaller validator set creates additional smart contract risks to consider."},{"question":"What are the typical funding rate spreads between Aevo and major CEXes for PENDLE?","answer":"PENDLE funding rates on Aevo typically trade 15-25 basis points higher than Binance during normal conditions, expanding to 50+ basis points during DeFi yield events. The premium reflects Aevo's DeFi-native user base and smaller liquidity pool compared to centralized exchanges."}]}]
